# Coding Standards – Image Gallery SPA

**Apply on every task.** Full details in `docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md`

## How to work efficiently

1. Identify task type (UI / API / test)
2. Read only the relevant sections from docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md (see index in §1)
3. Use general best practices for React, Next.js, Vitest

## Mandatory Rules

### No hardcoding
- **Copy:** Use constants or config in `src/lib/constants.ts`
- **Colors:** Use Tailwind / design tokens from `globals.css`. No hardcoded hex/rgb
- **Magic values:** Use named constants

### Code style
- **No inline styles:** Tailwind only
- **Images:** Use Next.js `<Image>` from `next/image`
- **Types:** No `any`. Define interfaces for props
- **File size:** Keep files under 300 lines

### Quality
- **ESLint:** Code must pass `npm run lint`
- **Prettier:** Run `npm run format` before commit
- **SonarQube:** Must pass `npm run sonar` if run

## Commit messages (Husky + Commitlint)

Format: `type(scope): subject`

- **Types:** feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, build, ci
- **Header max 100 chars**
- **Body:** Each line max 100 chars
- **Example:** `feat(gallery): add infinite scroll`

## Project structure

- `src/app/` – App Router pages
- `src/components/` – Shared components
- `src/lib/` – Utils, hooks, constants, mock data
- `__tests__/` – Test files

## When you need full detail

Read `docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md` for the relevant sections only (see index in §1)
